{"parse":{"title":"Winter Squid","pageid":24478,"wikitext":{"*":"__NOTOC__<onlyinclude>{{tooltip\n|mode={{{mode|}}}\n|arg={{{arg|}}}\n|icon=INV_Misc_Fish_13\n|name=Winter Squid\n|quality=common\n|level=35\n|effect=<u>Use</u>: Restores 1,215 health over 25 sec. Must remain seated while eating.\n|sell={{cost|||7}}\n|ilvl=45\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n'''Winter Squid''' prefer colder waters and only come near the shore during the winter.\n\n==Source==\n'''Winter Squid''' can be caught in the waters of [[Feralas]], [[Tanaris]], [[Azshara]], and the [[Hinterlands]] in the wintertime.\n\n==Winter Squid as an Ingredient==\n===[[Cooking]]===\n*[[Grilled Squid]]\n\n==Notes==\nThis squid is seasonal, meaning it is only available during winter months, starting with the 23rd of September each year. In addition, this type of \"fish\" has a daytime preference, meaning it has the best catchrate during 12.00-18.00 server time.\n\n==External links==\n<!-- Read http://www.wowwiki.com/WoWWiki:External_links before posting your links here.\nLinks that do not conform to the rules will be DELETED.\nRepeat violations may result in a BAN.\nHave a nice day. :) -->\n{{elinks-item|13755}}\n{{Elink|link=http://www.elsanglin.com/fish/winter_squid.html |site=El's Extreme Anglin' |icon=elsanglin}}\n[[Category:World of Warcraft cooking ingredient items]]\n[[Category:World of Warcraft food items]]\n[[Category:World of Warcraft common fished items]]\n[[Category:Squid]]"}}}